The paper discusses methodologies for discretizing robot paths and proposes a hybrid force/motion control system for adjusting robot paths with external sensory feedback. These topics are closely related to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of 3-D CAD drawings, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Fuzzy-PI control system involves the use of fuzzy logic, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on increasing the robot's autonomy suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
